{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018H9iSVxSX27VcEqHhutJFX","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me provide you with a comprehensive report of the repository structure.\n\n## Repository Overview\n\n### Directory Structure\n\n```\n/workspace/\n├── .agent-runner/\n│   └── implementer.log\n├── .github/\n│   └── workflows/\n│       └── release.yml\n├── .git/                          (git repository)\n├── .gitignore\n├── src/                           (source files)\n│   ├── Kanbamd.ts\n│   ├── errors.ts\n│   ├── helpers.ts\n│   ├── index.ts\n│   ├── storage.ts\n│   └── types.ts\n├── test/\n│   └── Kanbamd.test.ts\n├── scripts/\n│   └── release.mjs\n├── package.json\n├── package-lock.json\n├── tsconfig.json\n├── tsconfig.typecheck.json\n├── vitest.config.ts\n├── biome.json\n└── README.md\n```\n\n### package.json\n\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"@alejandrocantero/kanbamd\",\n  \"version\": \"1.4.3\",\n  \"description\": \"Manage Kanban boards backed by Markdown files, frontmatter, and column folders.\",\n  \"type\": \"module\",\n  \"main\": \"./dist/index.js\",\n  \"types\": \"./dist/index.d.ts\",\n  \"exports\": {\n    \".\": {\n      \"types\": \"./dist/index.d.ts\",\n      \"import\": \"./dist/index.js\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"files\": [\n    \"dist\"\n  ],\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"build\": \"tsc -p tsconfig.json\",\n    \"format\": \"biome format . --write\",\n    \"lint\": \"biome check .\",\n    \"lint:fix\": \"biome check . --write\",\n    \"release\": \"node scripts/release.mjs\",\n    \"test\": \"vitest run\",\n    \"typecheck\": \"tsc -p tsconfig.typecheck.json\"\n  },\n  \"keywords\": [\n    \"kanban\",\n    \"markdown\",\n    \"frontmatter\",\n    \"typescript\"\n  ],\n  \"license\": \"MIT\",\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"fuse.js\": \"^7.1.0\",\n    \"gray-matter\": \"^4.0.3\",\n    \"slugify\": \"^1.6.6\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"@biomejs/biome\": \"^1.9.4\",\n    \"@types/node\": \"^20.12.12\",\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.4.5\",\n    \"vitest\": \"^1.6.0\"\n  },\n  \"engines\": {\n    \"node\": \">=20\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### tsconfig.json\n\n```json\n{\n  \"compilerOptions\": {\n    \"target\": \"ES2022\",\n    \"lib\": [\"ES2022\"],\n    \"module\": \"NodeNext\",\n    \"moduleResolution\": \"NodeNext\",\n    \"strict\": true,\n    \"declaration\": true,\n    \"declarationMap\": true,\n    \"sourceMap\": true,\n    \"outDir\": \"dist\",\n    \"rootDir\": \"src\",\n    \"skipLibCheck\": true\n  },\n  \"include\": [\"src/**/*.ts\"]\n}\n```\n\n### README.md\n\nThe repository is a TypeScript package for managing Kanban boards stored as Markdown files with frontmatter and column folders. The README includes:\n\n- Installation instructions\n- Board layout explanation\n- Card format with frontmatter fields (title, tags, order, priority)\n- Usage examples showing how to create, move, and search cards\n- Memory storage option\n- Documentation of reserved frontmatter fields (title, tags, order)\n\n### Source Files\n\n#### /workspace/src/index.ts\nExports the main `Kanbamd` class and type definitions (errors, card types, options, etc.)\n\n#### /workspace/src/Kanbamd.ts\nMain class (358 lines) implementing the Kanban board logic with methods:\n- `init()` - Initialize the board\n- `listColumns()` - Get all columns\n- `listCards()` - List cards, optionally filtered by column\n- `getCard()` - Get a specific card\n- `createCard()` - Create a new card\n- `updateCard()` - Update card content\n- `moveCard()` - Move card between columns\n- `reorderCard()` - Reorder cards within a column\n- `deleteCard()` - Delete a card\n- `searchCards()` - Search cards with fuzzy matching and tag filtering\n- Private methods for managing card order, validation, and queue handling\n\n#### /workspace/src/types.ts\nType definitions including:\n- `ReservedFrontmatterKey` - \"title\", \"tags\", \"order\"\n- `ExtraFrontmatter` - Custom frontmatter object type\n- `BaseFrontmatter` - Core required frontmatter\n- `CardFrontmatter<T>` - Full frontmatter with custom fields\n- `Card<T>` - Complete card object\n- `CardLocator` - Column and ID reference\n- `CreateCardInput<T>` - Input for creating cards\n- `UpdateCardInput<T>` - Input for updating cards\n- `ListCardsOptions` - Filtering options\n- `SearchCardsOptions` - Search parameters\n- `StorageKind` - \"filesystem\" or \"memory\"\n- `KanbamdOptions` - Constructor options\n\n#### /workspace/src/errors.ts\nCustom error classes:\n- `KanbamdError` - Base error class\n- `BoardRootNotFoundError`\n- `ColumnNotFoundError`\n- `CardNotFoundError`\n- `DuplicateCardError`\n- `InvalidFrontmatterError`\n- `InvalidStorageConfigurationError`\n\n#### /workspace/src/helpers.ts\nUtility functions (110 lines):\n- `toFileName()` - Convert card ID to filename\n- `toId()` - Convert filename to card ID\n- `createSlug()` - Generate URL-friendly slug from title\n- `validateColumnName()` - Validate column names\n- `validateCardId()` - Validate card IDs\n- `validateTitle()` - Validate card titles\n- `validateTags()` - Validate tag arrays\n- `validateExtraFrontmatter()` - Validate custom frontmatter\n- `parseCardFrontmatter()` - Parse frontmatter from markdown\n- `stringifyCard()` - Serialize card to markdown\n- `assertBaseFrontmatter()` - Assert required frontmatter exists\n\n#### /workspace/src/storage.ts\nStorage abstraction layer (168 lines) with:\n- `StorageAdapter` interface defining storage contract\n- `FilesystemStorage` - File-based implementation using Node.js fs\n- `MemoryStorage` - In-memory implementation using Map\n- Both implement: init, listMarkdownFiles, readCard, writeCard, moveCard, deleteCard\n\n### Tests\n\n#### /workspace/test/Kanbamd.test.ts\nComprehensive test suite (201 lines) using Vitest with 7 test cases covering:\n- Card creation with unique slugs and automatic ordering\n- Card updates with reserved frontmatter protection\n- Input validation and error handling\n- Card moving and reordering with order normalization\n- Fuzzy search with tag filtering\n- Filesystem storage with root creation and validation\n- Markdown parsing validation\n\n### Configuration Files\n\n- **vitest.config.ts** - Test runner configuration\n- **biome.json** - Code formatter and linter configuration (Biome)\n- **.gitignore** - Excludes node_modules, dist, .idea, .DS_Store\n\n### Additional Files\n\n- **tsconfig.typecheck.json** - Secondary TypeScript configuration (likely for type checking)\n- **scripts/release.mjs** - Release automation script\n- **.github/workflows/release.yml** - GitHub Actions workflow for releases"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d22e3197-cafa-48fe-8f3e-bcff61c66b02","uuid":"d22db487-72a5-43e4-8a54-aee64779c6d6","timestamp":"2026-05-03T16:51:23.968Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the repository at /workspace. I need a complete picture of:\n1. The directory structure (all files and folders)\n2. The contents of package.json\n3. The contents of any README files\n4. Any existing TypeScript/JavaScript source files\n5. Any existing CLI-related code\n6. The tsconfig.json if it exists\n7. Any existing tests\n\nReport back all file paths and the full contents of package.json, tsconfig.json, and README.md. Also show me the contents of any source files in src/.","agentId":"a3c14759024631bd3","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me provide you with a comprehensive report of the repository structure.\n\n## Repository Overview\n\n### Directory Structure\n\n```\n/workspace/\n├── .agent-runner/\n│   └── implementer.log\n├── .github/\n│   └── workflows/\n│       └── release.yml\n├── .git/                          (git repository)\n├── .gitignore\n├── src/                           (source files)\n│   ├── Kanbamd.ts\n│   ├── errors.ts\n│   ├── helpers.ts\n│   ├── index.ts\n│   ├── storage.ts\n│   └── types.ts\n├── test/\n│   └── Kanbamd.test.ts\n├── scripts/\n│   └── release.mjs\n├── package.json\n├── package-lock.json\n├── tsconfig.json\n├── tsconfig.typecheck.json\n├── vitest.config.ts\n├── biome.json\n└── README.md\n```\n\n### package.json\n\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"@alejandrocantero/kanbamd\",\n  \"version\": \"1.4.3\",\n  \"description\": \"Manage Kanban boards backed by Markdown files, frontmatter, and column folders.\",\n  \"type\": \"module\",\n  \"main\": \"./dist/index.js\",\n  \"types\": \"./dist/index.d.ts\",\n  \"exports\": {\n    \".\": {\n      \"types\": \"./dist/index.d.ts\",\n      \"import\": \"./dist/index.js\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"files\": [\n    \"dist\"\n  ],\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"build\": \"tsc -p tsconfig.json\",\n    \"format\": \"biome format . --write\",\n    \"lint\": \"biome check .\",\n    \"lint:fix\": \"biome check . --write\",\n    \"release\": \"node scripts/release.mjs\",\n    \"test\": \"vitest run\",\n    \"typecheck\": \"tsc -p tsconfig.typecheck.json\"\n  },\n  \"keywords\": [\n    \"kanban\",\n    \"markdown\",\n    \"frontmatter\",\n    \"typescript\"\n  ],\n  \"license\": \"MIT\",\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"fuse.js\": \"^7.1.0\",\n    \"gray-matter\": \"^4.0.3\",\n    \"slugify\": \"^1.6.6\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"@biomejs/biome\": \"^1.9.4\",\n    \"@types/node\": \"^20.12.12\",\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.4.5\",\n    \"vitest\": \"^1.6.0\"\n  },\n  \"engines\": {\n    \"node\": \">=20\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### tsconfig.json\n\n```json\n{\n  \"compilerOptions\": {\n    \"target\": \"ES2022\",\n    \"lib\": [\"ES2022\"],\n    \"module\": \"NodeNext\",\n    \"moduleResolution\": \"NodeNext\",\n    \"strict\": true,\n    \"declaration\": true,\n    \"declarationMap\": true,\n    \"sourceMap\": true,\n    \"outDir\": \"dist\",\n    \"rootDir\": \"src\",\n    \"skipLibCheck\": true\n  },\n  \"include\": [\"src/**/*.ts\"]\n}\n```\n\n### README.md\n\nThe repository is a TypeScript package for managing Kanban boards stored as Markdown files with frontmatter and column folders. The README includes:\n\n- Installation instructions\n- Board layout explanation\n- Card format with frontmatter fields (title, tags, order, priority)\n- Usage examples showing how to create, move, and search cards\n- Memory storage option\n- Documentation of reserved frontmatter fields (title, tags, order)\n\n### Source Files\n\n#### /workspace/src/index.ts\nExports the main `Kanbamd` class and type definitions (errors, card types, options, etc.)\n\n#### /workspace/src/Kanbamd.ts\nMain class (358 lines) implementing the Kanban board logic with methods:\n- `init()` - Initialize the board\n- `listColumns()` - Get all columns\n- `listCards()` - List cards, optionally filtered by column\n- `getCard()` - Get a specific card\n- `createCard()` - Create a new card\n- `updateCard()` - Update card content\n- `moveCard()` - Move card between columns\n- `reorderCard()` - Reorder cards within a column\n- `deleteCard()` - Delete a card\n- `searchCards()` - Search cards with fuzzy matching and tag filtering\n- Private methods for managing card order, validation, and queue handling\n\n#### /workspace/src/types.ts\nType definitions including:\n- `ReservedFrontmatterKey` - \"title\", \"tags\", \"order\"\n- `ExtraFrontmatter` - Custom frontmatter object type\n- `BaseFrontmatter` - Core required frontmatter\n- `CardFrontmatter<T>` - Full frontmatter with custom fields\n- `Card<T>` - Complete card object\n- `CardLocator` - Column and ID reference\n- `CreateCardInput<T>` - Input for creating cards\n- `UpdateCardInput<T>` - Input for updating cards\n- `ListCardsOptions` - Filtering options\n- `SearchCardsOptions` - Search parameters\n- `StorageKind` - \"filesystem\" or \"memory\"\n- `KanbamdOptions` - Constructor options\n\n#### /workspace/src/errors.ts\nCustom error classes:\n- `KanbamdError` - Base error class\n- `BoardRootNotFoundError`\n- `ColumnNotFoundError`\n- `CardNotFoundError`\n- `DuplicateCardError`\n- `InvalidFrontmatterError`\n- `InvalidStorageConfigurationError`\n\n#### /workspace/src/helpers.ts\nUtility functions (110 lines):\n- `toFileName()` - Convert card ID to filename\n- `toId()` - Convert filename to card ID\n- `createSlug()` - Generate URL-friendly slug from title\n- `validateColumnName()` - Validate column names\n- `validateCardId()` - Validate card IDs\n- `validateTitle()` - Validate card titles\n- `validateTags()` - Validate tag arrays\n- `validateExtraFrontmatter()` - Validate custom frontmatter\n- `parseCardFrontmatter()` - Parse frontmatter from markdown\n- `stringifyCard()` - Serialize card to markdown\n- `assertBaseFrontmatter()` - Assert required frontmatter exists\n\n#### /workspace/src/storage.ts\nStorage abstraction layer (168 lines) with:\n- `StorageAdapter` interface defining storage contract\n- `FilesystemStorage` - File-based implementation using Node.js fs\n- `MemoryStorage` - In-memory implementation using Map\n- Both implement: init, listMarkdownFiles, readCard, writeCard, moveCard, deleteCard\n\n### Tests\n\n#### /workspace/test/Kanbamd.test.ts\nComprehensive test suite (201 lines) using Vitest with 7 test cases covering:\n- Card creation with unique slugs and automatic ordering\n- Card updates with reserved frontmatter protection\n- Input validation and error handling\n- Card moving and reordering with order normalization\n- Fuzzy search with tag filtering\n- Filesystem storage with root creation and validation\n- Markdown parsing validation\n\n### Configuration Files\n\n- **vitest.config.ts** - Test runner configuration\n- **biome.json** - Code formatter and linter configuration (Biome)\n- **.gitignore** - Excludes node_modules, dist, .idea, .DS_Store\n\n### Additional Files\n\n- **tsconfig.typecheck.json** - Secondary TypeScript configuration (likely for type checking)\n- **scripts/release.mjs** - Release automation script\n- **.github/workflows/release.yml** - GitHub Actions workflow for releases"}],"totalDurationMs":21231,"totalTokens":33487,"totalToolUseCount":15,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3112,"cache_read_input_tok